The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Prabir Roy, who mowed down seven-year-old Gaurav Banerjee and injured five persons in Thakurpukur on Tuesday, was produced before the sub-divisional judicial magistrate?s court in Alipore on Wednesday. He has been remanded in judicial custody till July 22. Roy was driving a Maruti Omni, though he did not have a licence. The vehicle?s driver, who was sitting beside Roy during the mishap, has also been remanded in judicial custody.

 udhir Sarkar, a member of the managing committee of Gaurav?s school, said he would ask police to ensure safe movement of vehicles in the area where the accident occurred. The condition of Gaurav?s father, Asish Banerjee, and the other four injured is stable, doctors said. 

 A three-ft-long weather balloon fell from the skies and held up traffic for more than 40 minutes at Esplanade on Wednesday evening. People ran for safety, fearing that the balloon could contain a bomb. Even a team from the bomb disposal squad was sent for. The balloon, sent up to measure wind speed and direction by the meteorological department, fell a few yards from the east gate of Raj Bhavan. 

 Two persons were killed in road accidents in Howrah between late Tuesday and Wednesday evening. Police said the cleaner of an oil tanker died when the vehicle turned turtle on Mumbai Road, near Nibra (under Domjur police station), around 4 pm on Wednesday. The tanker was impounded, but the driver fled. In the other mishap, Vicky Sharma, 25, was knocked down by a truck while he was crossing a road near Bankim Setu around 11.30 pm on Tuesday. Sharma, a resident of the Bangabashi area, in Howrah, died on the spot. The truck driver has been arrested and the vehicle impounded.

 Ranjan Kumar was arrested in Garden Reach on Wednesday for sitting for a railway recruitment board test allegedly with fake papers.

 The CESC on Wednesday snapped the power connection of two junior high schools of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation (CMC), in Topsia, for ?non-payment of bills?. Kaji Nazrul Islam School and Allhama Iqbal Urdu Junior High School together have 1,400 students. The teachers threatened to organise a demonstration in front of the CMC headquarters on SN Banerjee Road, if the supply was not restored within three days.

 The Calcutta Municipal Corporation on Wednesday distributed more than 5,000 saplings and shrubs from its office on SN Banerjee Road. Mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharya distributed some saplings in the morning. Officials said the response was ?overwhelming?. Mayoral council member (parks and gardens) Faiyaz Ahmed Khan said even people from the districts had turned up to collect the saplings.

 L.C. Bihani was elected president of the high court Bar Association on Wednesday. Amal Kumar Mukherjee was elected general secretary. Bihani takes over from Sardar Amjad Ali and Mukherjee from Chandi Charan Chakraborty.

 Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will dedicate BP Poddar Hospital to the people on July 24, a hospital official said. 

 The panchayat and rural development department and the animal resources development department will organise a seminar on ?Animal Resources and Rural Development? at Swasthya Bhavan, Salt Lake, on July 21. 

